---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section class="landing">
    <h1>BeaconGuard Assurance</h1>
    <p class="hero-subheadline">
      Deterministic governance between enterprise applications and AI/model endpoints.
    </p>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is a runtime control plane for enterprise AI operations.
      It enforces policy decisions consistently, records reviewable evidence,
      and makes trust boundaries explicit.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Explore the platform</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/design-partner-program">Apply for design partner review</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why BeaconGuard Exists</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprise AI systems often fail the same question under pressure:
      when outcomes need to be explained months later, what exactly was authorized,
      who decided it, and what evidence remains?
    </p>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard exists where application-level logs are not enough.
      It brings authorization intent and enforcement outcomes into a durable, deterministic boundary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What BeaconGuard Does</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard operates as an externalized control plane that sits between
      enterprise systems and AI endpoints.
    </p>
    <p>
      Authorization logic is removed from applications and enforced independently
      using signed, versioned policy artifacts.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every request gets a deterministic governance decision and a reviewable evidence record.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Core Platform Outcomes</h2>
    <div class="section-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Deterministic Control</h3>
        <p>The same input and policy context produce the same authorization outcome every time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Operational Governance</h3>
        <p>Policy evaluation is centralized into infrastructure logic separate from model behavior.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Evidence for Review</h3>
        <p>Decision context and outcomes are emitted in formats designed for audit and incident review.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Where BeaconGuard Sits in the Stack</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard sits in the runtime path between your applications and AI/model providers.
      Applications submit normalized authorization context, BeaconGuard evaluates policy,
      and the decision returns as an explicit allow/deny signal.
    </p>
    <p>
      This preserves enterprise logic in a dedicated governance layer, while your core systems
      remain focused on product workflows.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/how-it-works">Understand the decision flow</a></p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
    <p>BeaconGuard is for organizations that run AI inside production systems where:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>authorization outcomes must be explainable and repeatable,</li>
      <li>decision evidence must be reviewable after the fact, and</li>
      <li>governance must be enforced independent of prompt or model implementation.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Design Partner Positioning</h2>
    <p>
      We work with teams that are building regulated AI workflows and want to
      validate governance patterns before broad rollout.
    </p>
    <p>
      Design partners help shape practical policy and evidence requirements that match real operational constraints.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/design-partner-program">Learn about BeaconGuard design partners</a></p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Get Started</h2>
    <p>
      Start with platform goals and architecture fit, then move into technical depth as needed.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Review the platform scope</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Talk to BeaconGuard</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>